At Athens Virgil met with Augustus, who was returning from Samos, where hc γ had wintered after his Syrian expedition, to Rome. Changing his former in- tention, Virgil determined to accompany his patron. On a visit to Megara he was seized with a sudden indisposition, which his voyage increased, and he died a few days after his arrival at Brundusium, in his fifty-second year.
